
this is how the project structure of an e-commerce application can be organized in a clean and modular way. Each module (user, product, category, cart, order, payment) has its own sub-packages for entity, 
dto, mapper, repository, service, and controller. Additionally, there are common packages for security and configuration, as well as a common package for exceptions and utilities. This structure promotes
 separation of concerns and makes the codebase easier to maintain and scale.
